[{"id":"VH979938","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div>\n<div class=\"stimulus_reference\">\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure presents the cross section of three long wires arranged in an equilateral triangle, which are wires A, B, and C respectively. The line between wires A and B forms the horizontal top edge of the triangle. The current through wires A and C are directed into the page. The current through wire B is directed out of the page. The point P is indicated, which is directly to the left of wire C and directly below wire A.\" height=\"93\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VH979938.g21.png\" width=\"150\" /></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Three long wires, each with currents of the same magnitude, are arranged so that they are equidistant from each other, and in a cross-sectional view they form an equilateral triangle as shown above. Two of the wires, <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"A\"><math alttext=\"A\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>A</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"C\"><math alttext=\"C\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>C</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>, have currents directed into the page, and wire <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B\"><math alttext=\"B\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>B</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> has a current directed out of the page. Which of the following best represents the direction of the net magnetic field at point <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"P\"><math alttext=\"P\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>P</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> that is directly below wire <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"A\"><math alttext=\"A\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>A</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> and to the left of wire <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"C\"><math alttext=\"C\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>C</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> ?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VH979938_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"inline_image\"></span></p>\n\n\n<span class=\"inline_image\"><img alt=\"The figure presents an arrow that points vertically upward.\" height=\"92\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VH979938.g15.png\" width=\"45\"></span>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"inline_image\"><img alt=\"The figure presents an arrow that points downward and to the right.\" height=\"46\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VH979938.g16.png\" width=\"45\"></span></p>\n","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"inline_image\"><img alt=\"The figure presents an arrow that points vertically downward.\" height=\"89\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VH979938.g17.png\" width=\"45\"></span></p>\n","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"inline_image\"><img alt=\"The figure presents an arrow that points horizontally to the left.\" height=\"16\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VH979938.g18.png\" width=\"45\"></span></p>\n","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"inline_image\"><img alt=\"The figure presents an arrow that points up and to the left.\" height=\"50\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VH979938.g19.png\" width=\"45\"></span></p>\n"],"answer":4}]